{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RRzzuR9Gza2VnP1FVUGuya","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.web;\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.counter.api.OrderService;\n     5→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.commands.PlaceOrderCommand;\n     6→import io.vertx.mutiny.core.eventbus.EventBus;\n     7→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n     8→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n     9→\n    10→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    11→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    17→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    18→\n    19→@Path(\"/api\")\n    20→@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    21→@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    22→public class CoffeeshopApiResource {\n    23→\n    24→    private static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(CoffeeshopApiResource.class);\n    25→\n    26→    @Inject\n    27→    OrderService orderService;\n    28→\n    29→    @Inject\n    30→    EventBus eventBus;\n    31→\n    32→    @POST\n    33→    @Path(\"/order\")\n    34→    @Transactional\n    35→    public Response placeOrder(final PlaceOrderCommand placeOrderCommand) {\n    36→\n    37→        LOGGER.info(\"PlaceOrderCommand received: {}\", placeOrderCommand);\n    38→        orderService.onOrderIn(placeOrderCommand);\n    39→        return Response.accepted().build();\n    40→    }\n    41→\n    42→    @POST\n    43→    @Path(\"/message\")\n    44→    public void sendMessage(final String message) {\n    45→//        webUpdater.send(message);\n    46→        LOGGER.debug(\"received message: {}\", message);\n    47→        LOGGER.debug(\"sending to web-updates: {}\", message);\n    48→        eventBus.publish(\"web-updates\", message);\n    49→    }\n    50→\n    51→}\n    52→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fccccfb6-6c3c-4161-b41c-50ffcb4f1374","uuid":"5eb65fad-8f4f-4a8b-a2d8-0204032e84f7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011BHUZPMUDKd2HecmagTn6H","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.web;\n     2→\n     3→import io.smallrye.mutiny.Multi;\n     4→import io.vertx.mutiny.core.eventbus.EventBus;\n     5→import io.vertx.mutiny.core.eventbus.Message;\n     6→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n     7→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n     8→\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    14→\n    15→import static io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.infrastructure.EventBusTopics.WEB_UPDATES;\n    16→\n    17→@Path(\"/dashboard\")\n    18→public class DashboardEndpoint {\n    19→\n    20→    private static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(DashboardEndpoint.class);\n    21→\n    22→    @Inject\n    23→    EventBus eventBus;\n    24→\n    25→    @GET\n    26→    @Path(\"/stream\")\n    27→    @Produces(MediaType.SERVER_SENT_EVENTS)\n    28→    public Multi<String> dashboardStream() {\n    29→\n    30→        return eventBus.<String>consumer(WEB_UPDATES)\n    31→                .toMulti()\n    32→                .map(Message::body);\n    33→    }\n    34→\n    35→}\n    36→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fccccfb6-6c3c-4161-b41c-50ffcb4f1374","uuid":"eee58b50-db37-4a44-a7c3-b8afc3c664ca"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01N1XEmGNzswrUzctxsiNZUn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.web;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.qute.Template;\n     4→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n     5→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.counter.api.OrderService;\n     6→import org.eclipse.microprofile.config.inject.ConfigProperty;\n     7→\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    13→\n    14→@Path(\"/\")\n    15→public class WebResource {\n    16→\n    17→    @ConfigProperty(name=\"streamUrl\")\n    18→    String streamUrl;\n    19→\n    20→    @ConfigProperty(name=\"storeId\")\n    21→    String storeId;\n    22→\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    OrderService orderService;\n    25→\n    26→    @Inject\n    27→    Template coffeeshopTemplate;\n    28→\n    29→    @GET\n    30→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    31→    public TemplateInstance getIndex(){\n    32→\n    33→        return coffeeshopTemplate\n    34→                .data(\"streamUrl\", streamUrl)\n    35→                .data(\"storeId\", storeId);\n    36→    }\n    37→}\n    38→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fccccfb6-6c3c-4161-b41c-50ffcb4f1374","uuid":"1fa0ef19-7665-4e74-9301-3d32e2a1ad79"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PU8FyoKFbMRomkshRiGHfm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.barista;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.runtime.Startup;\n     4→import io.quarkus.vertx.ConsumeEvent;\n     5→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.barista.api.Barista;\n     6→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.barista.domain.BaristaItem;\n     7→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.barista.domain.BaristaRepository;\n     8→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Item;\n     9→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderIn;\n    10→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderUp;\n    11→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.utils.JsonUtil;\n    12→import io.smallrye.common.annotation.Blocking;\n    13→import io.vertx.core.eventbus.EventBus;\n    14→import io.vertx.mutiny.core.eventbus.Message;\n    15→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n    16→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n    17→\n    18→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    19→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    20→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    21→import java.time.Instant;\n    22→\n    23→import static io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.infrastructure.EventBusTopics.BARISTA_IN;\n    24→import static io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.infrastructure.EventBusTopics.ORDERS_UP;\n    25→\n    26→//@Startup @ApplicationScoped\n    27→public class BaristaImpl {\n    28→\n    29→    private static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(BaristaImpl.class);\n    30→\n    31→    private final String madeBy = \"Mr. Spock\";\n    32→\n    33→    @Inject\n    34→    EventBus eventBus;\n    35→\n    36→    @Inject\n    37→    BaristaRepository baristaRepository;\n    38→\n    39→//    @ConsumeEvent(BARISTA_IN) @Blocking @Transactional\n    40→    public void onOrderIn(final Message message) {\n    41→        OrderIn orderIn = JsonUtil.fromJson(message.body().toString(), OrderIn.class);\n    42→        BaristaItem baristaItem = new BaristaItem();\n    43→        baristaItem.setItem(orderIn.item.toString());\n    44→        baristaItem.setTimeIn(Instant.now());\n    45→        LOGGER.debug(\"order in : {}\", orderIn);\n    46→        try {\n    47→            Thread.sleep(calculateDelay(orderIn.item));\n    48→        } catch (InterruptedException e) {\n    49→            e.printStackTrace();\n    50→        }\n    51→        OrderUp orderUp = new OrderUp(\n    52→                orderIn.orderId,\n    53→                orderIn.itemId,\n    54→                orderIn.item,\n    55→                orderIn.name,\n    56→                Instant.now(),\n    57→                madeBy);\n    58→        baristaItem.setTimeUp(Instant.now());\n    59→        baristaRepository.persist(baristaItem);\n    60→        eventBus.<OrderUp>publish(ORDERS_UP, JsonUtil.toJson(orderUp));\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→//    @Override\n    64→//    public void onRemakeIn(Message remakeMessage) {\n    65→//\n    66→//    }\n    67→//\n    68→//    @Override\n    69→//    public void onCancelOrder(Message cancellationMessage) {\n    70→//\n    71→//    }\n    72→\n    73→    private int calculateDelay(final Item item) {\n    74→        switch (item) {\n    75→            case COFFEE_BLACK:\n    76→                return 5000;\n    77→            case COFFEE_WITH_ROOM:\n    78→                return 5000;\n    79→            case ESPRESSO:\n    80→                return 7000;\n    81→            case ESPRESSO_DOUBLE:\n    82→                return 7000;\n    83→            case CAPPUCCINO:\n    84→                return 10000;\n    85→            default:\n    86→                return 3000;\n    87→        }\n    88→    }\n    89→\n    90→}\n    91→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fccccfb6-6c3c-4161-b41c-50ffcb4f1374","uuid":"bd1a991a-45e2-4fac-b500-772086528cc1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HQKUPXvmyAbwo6UVoJzz2M","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.barista;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.runtime.Startup;\n     4→import io.quarkus.vertx.ConsumeEvent;\n     5→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.barista.api.Barista;\n     6→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.barista.domain.BaristaRepository;\n     7→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderIn;\n     8→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderUp;\n     9→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.utils.JsonUtil;\n    10→import io.smallrye.common.annotation.Blocking;\n    11→import io.vertx.core.eventbus.EventBus;\n    12→import io.vertx.mutiny.core.eventbus.Message;\n    13→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Channel;\n    14→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Emitter;\n    15→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n    16→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n    17→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n    18→\n    19→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n    20→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    21→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    22→\n    23→import static io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.infrastructure.EventBusTopics.BARISTA_IN;\n    24→import static io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.infrastructure.EventBusTopics.ORDERS_UP;\n    25→\n    26→@Startup @ApplicationScoped\n    27→public class BaristaOutpostImpl implements Barista {\n    28→\n    29→    static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(BaristaOutpostImpl.class);\n    30→\n    31→    @Channel(\"barista-outpost\")\n    32→    Emitter<OrderIn> baristaEmitter;\n    33→\n    34→    @Inject\n    35→    EventBus eventBus;\n    36→\n    37→    @ConsumeEvent(BARISTA_IN) @Blocking @Transactional\n    38→    public void onOrderIn(final Message orderInMessage) {\n    39→        baristaEmitter.send(JsonUtil.fromJsonToOrderIn(orderInMessage.body().toString()));\n    40→    }\n    41→\n    42→    @Override\n    43→    public void onRemakeIn(final Message remakeMessage) {\n    44→        baristaEmitter.send(JsonUtil.fromJsonToOrderIn(remakeMessage.body().toString()));\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    @Override\n    48→    public void onCancelOrder(final Message cancellationMessage) {\n    49→        baristaEmitter.send(JsonUtil.fromJsonToOrderIn(cancellationMessage.body().toString()));\n    50→    }\n    51→\n    52→    @Incoming(\"orders-up\")  @Blocking @Transactional\n    53→    public void onOrderUp(OrderUp orderUp) {\n    54→        LOGGER.debug(\"OrderUp: {}\", orderUp);\n    55→        eventBus.<OrderUp>publish(ORDERS_UP, JsonUtil.toJson(orderUp));\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→}\n    59→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fccccfb6-6c3c-4161-b41c-50ffcb4f1374","uuid":"1bf93aeb-16b4-46d8-93e7-887c3996f161"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WxuH1546Zn2YbsYi7Yf94E","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.barista.api;\n     2→\n     3→import io.vertx.mutiny.core.eventbus.Message;\n     4→\n     5→public interface Barista {\n     6→\n     7→    /**\n     8→     * Message with a JSON payload corresponding to OrderIn value object\n     9→     *\n    10→     * @param orderInMessage OrderIn\n    11→     * @see io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects.OrderIn\n    12→     */\n    13→    public void onOrderIn(final Message orderInMessage);\n    14→\n    15→    public void onRemakeIn(final Message remakeMessage);\n    16→\n    17→    public void onCancelOrder(final Message cancellationMessage);\n    18→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fccccfb6-6c3c-4161-b41c-50ffcb4f1374","uuid":"6e560ebc-56f9-4859-a627-424c9cd9862d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NSMmYzW22wfuHooFbQXiuQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.barista.domain;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheEntity;\n     4→\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n     7→import java.time.Instant;\n     8→\n     9→@Entity @Table(name = \"barista_order\", schema = \"barista\")\n    10→public class BaristaItem extends PanacheEntity {\n    11→\n    12→    private String item;\n    13→\n    14→    private Instant timeIn;\n    15→\n    16→    private Instant timeUp;\n    17→\n    18→    public BaristaItem(String item, Instant timeIn, Instant timeUp) {\n    19→        this.item = item;\n    20→        this.timeIn = timeIn;\n    21→        this.timeUp = timeUp;\n    22→    }\n    23→\n    24→    public BaristaItem() {\n    25→    }\n    26→\n    27→    @Override\n    28→    public String toString() {\n    29→        final StringBuilder stringBuilder = new StringBuilder(\"BaristaItem{\");\n    30→        stringBuilder.append(\"item='\").append(item).append('\\'');\n    31→        stringBuilder.append(\", timeIn=\").append(timeIn);\n    32→        stringBuilder.append(\", timeUp=\").append(timeUp);\n    33→        stringBuilder.append('}');\n    34→        return stringBuilder.toString();\n    35→    }\n    36→\n    37→    @Override\n    38→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    39→        if (this == o) return true;\n    40→        if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;\n    41→\n    42→        BaristaItem that = (BaristaItem) o;\n    43→\n    44→        if (item != null ? !item.equals(that.item) : that.item != null) return false;\n    45→        if (timeIn != null ? !timeIn.equals(that.timeIn) : that.timeIn != null) return false;\n    46→        return timeUp != null ? timeUp.equals(that.timeUp) : that.timeUp == null;\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    @Override\n    50→    public int hashCode() {\n    51→        int result = item != null ? item.hashCode() : 0;\n    52→        result = 31 * result + (timeIn != null ? timeIn.hashCode() : 0);\n    53→        result = 31 * result + (timeUp != null ? timeUp.hashCode() : 0);\n    54→        return result;\n    55→    }\n    56→\n    57→    public String getItem() {\n    58→        return item;\n    59→    }\n    60→\n    61→    public void setItem(String item) {\n    62→        this.item = item;\n    63→    }\n    64→\n    65→    public Instant getTimeIn() {\n    66→        return timeIn;\n    67→    }\n    68→\n    69→    public void setTimeIn(Instant timeIn) {\n    70→        this.timeIn = timeIn;\n    71→    }\n    72→\n    73→    public Instant getTimeUp() {\n    74→        return timeUp;\n    75→    }\n    76→\n    77→    public void setTimeUp(Instant timeUp) {\n    78→        this.timeUp = timeUp;\n    79→    }\n    80→}\n    81→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fccccfb6-6c3c-4161-b41c-50ffcb4f1374","uuid":"89d4f668-4682-4384-9817-0fd260933abb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SmYXgMSrin3CC9ngvGo8JS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.barista.domain;\n     2→\n     3→import io.agroal.api.AgroalDataSource;\n     4→import io.quarkus.agroal.DataSource;\n     5→import io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheRepository;\n     6→\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→\n    10→@ApplicationScoped\n    11→public class BaristaRepository implements PanacheRepository<BaristaItem> {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    @DataSource(\"barista\")\n    15→    AgroalDataSource baristaDatasource;\n    16→\n    17→}\n    18→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fccccfb6-6c3c-4161-b41c-50ffcb4f1374","uuid":"d38033cd-6351-4307-83b7-50ffdaf30944"}
