{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XuMDYDekr7mTkoM8fQSeFX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.commands;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonProperty;\n     4→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Item;\n     5→\n     6→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n     7→import java.util.StringJoiner;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * Representst the individual line items in a PlaceOrderCommand\n    11→ */\n    12→public class CommandItem {\n    13→\n    14→    public final Item item;\n    15→\n    16→    public final String name;\n    17→\n    18→    public final BigDecimal price;\n    19→\n    20→    public CommandItem(\n    21→            @JsonProperty(\"item\") Item item,\n    22→            @JsonProperty(\"name\") String name,\n    23→            @JsonProperty(\"price\") BigDecimal price) {\n    24→        this.item = item;\n    25→        this.name = name;\n    26→        this.price = price;\n    27→    }\n    28→\n    29→    @Override\n    30→    public String toString() {\n    31→        return new StringJoiner(\", \", CommandItem.class.getSimpleName() + \"[\", \"]\")\n    32→                .add(\"item=\" + item)\n    33→                .add(\"name='\" + name + \"'\")\n    34→                .add(\"price=\" + price)\n    35→                .toString();\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    @Override\n    39→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    40→        if (this == o) return true;\n    41→        if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;\n    42→\n    43→        CommandItem that = (CommandItem) o;\n    44→\n    45→        if (item != that.item) return false;\n    46→        if (name != null ? !name.equals(that.name) : that.name != null) return false;\n    47→        return price != null ? price.equals(that.price) : that.price == null;\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    @Override\n    51→    public int hashCode() {\n    52→        int result = item != null ? item.hashCode() : 0;\n    53→        result = 31 * result + (name != null ? name.hashCode() : 0);\n    54→        result = 31 * result + (price != null ? price.hashCode() : 0);\n    55→        return result;\n    56→    }\n    57→}\n    58→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fccccfb6-6c3c-4161-b41c-50ffcb4f1374","uuid":"a206b6a7-6c1f-41c7-a806-756f0f51334c"}
