{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HAEjKH8eLGkC8Boz75aW2x","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.commands;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonCreator;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonIgnore;\n     5→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonProperty;\n     6→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Location;\n     7→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.OrderSource;\n     8→\n     9→import java.time.Instant;\n    10→import java.util.List;\n    11→import java.util.Optional;\n    12→\n    13→public class PlaceOrderCommand {\n    14→\n    15→    private final CommandType commandType = CommandType.PLACE_ORDER;\n    16→\n    17→    private final String id;\n    18→\n    19→    private final OrderSource orderSource;\n    20→\n    21→    private final Location location;\n    22→\n    23→    private final String loyaltyMemberId;\n    24→\n    25→    private final List<CommandItem> baristaItems;\n    26→\n    27→    private final List<CommandItem> kitchenItems;\n    28→\n    29→    private final Instant timestamp;\n    30→\n    31→    @JsonCreator(mode = JsonCreator.Mode.PROPERTIES)\n    32→    public PlaceOrderCommand(\n    33→            @JsonProperty(\"id\") final String id,\n    34→            @JsonProperty(\"orderSource\") final OrderSource orderSource,\n    35→            @JsonProperty(\"storeId\") final Location location,\n    36→            @JsonProperty(\"rewardsId\") final Optional<String> loyaltyMemberId,\n    37→            @JsonProperty(\"baristaItems\") Optional<List<CommandItem>> baristaItems,\n    38→            @JsonProperty(\"kitchenItems\") Optional<List<CommandItem>> kitchenItems,\n    39→            @JsonProperty(\"commandType\") final CommandType commandType) {\n    40→        this.id = id;\n    41→        this.orderSource = orderSource;\n    42→        this.location = location;\n    43→        if (loyaltyMemberId.isPresent()) {\n    44→            this.loyaltyMemberId = loyaltyMemberId.get();\n    45→        }else{\n    46→            this.loyaltyMemberId = null;\n    47→        }\n    48→        if (baristaItems.isPresent()) {\n    49→            this.baristaItems = baristaItems.get();\n    50→        }else{\n    51→            this.baristaItems = null;\n    52→        }\n    53→        if (kitchenItems.isPresent()) {\n    54→            this.kitchenItems = kitchenItems.get();\n    55→        }else{\n    56→            this.kitchenItems = null;\n    57→        }\n    58→        this.timestamp = Instant.now();\n    59→    }\n    60→\n    61→    @Override\n    62→    public String toString() {\n    63→        return \"PlaceOrderCommand{\" +\n    64→                \"id='\" + id + '\\'' +\n    65→                \", orderSource=\" + orderSource +\n    66→                \", location=\" + location +\n    67→                \", loyaltyMemberId='\" + loyaltyMemberId + '\\'' +\n    68→                \", baristaItems=\" + baristaItems +\n    69→                \", kitchenItems=\" + kitchenItems +\n    70→                \", timestamp=\" + timestamp +\n    71→                '}';\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→    @Override\n    75→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    76→        if (this == o) return true;\n    77→        if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;\n    78→\n    79→        PlaceOrderCommand that = (PlaceOrderCommand) o;\n    80→\n    81→        if (id != null ? !id.equals(that.id) : that.id != null) return false;\n    82→        if (orderSource != that.orderSource) return false;\n    83→        if (location != that.location) return false;\n    84→        if (loyaltyMemberId != null ? !loyaltyMemberId.equals(that.loyaltyMemberId) : that.loyaltyMemberId != null)\n    85→            return false;\n    86→        if (baristaItems != null ? !baristaItems.equals(that.baristaItems) : that.baristaItems != null)\n    87→            return false;\n    88→        if (kitchenItems != null ? !kitchenItems.equals(that.kitchenItems) : that.kitchenItems != null)\n    89→            return false;\n    90→        return timestamp != null ? timestamp.equals(that.timestamp) : that.timestamp == null;\n    91→    }\n    92→\n    93→    @Override\n    94→    public int hashCode() {\n    95→        int result = id != null ? id.hashCode() : 0;\n    96→        result = 31 * result + (orderSource != null ? orderSource.hashCode() : 0);\n    97→        result = 31 * result + (location != null ? location.hashCode() : 0);\n    98→        result = 31 * result + (loyaltyMemberId != null ? loyaltyMemberId.hashCode() : 0);\n    99→        result = 31 * result + (baristaItems != null ? baristaItems.hashCode() : 0);\n   100→        result = 31 * result + (kitchenItems != null ? kitchenItems.hashCode() : 0);\n   101→        result = 31 * result + (timestamp != null ? timestamp.hashCode() : 0);\n   102→        return result;\n   103→    }\n   104→\n   105→    public Optional<List<CommandItem>> getBaristaItems() {\n   106→        return Optional.ofNullable(baristaItems);\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    public Optional<List<CommandItem>> getKitchenItems() {\n   110→        return Optional.ofNullable(kitchenItems);\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    public Optional<String> getLoyaltyMemberId() {\n   114→        return Optional.ofNullable(loyaltyMemberId);\n   115→    }\n   116→\n   117→    public String getId() {\n   118→        return id;\n   119→    }\n   120→\n   121→    public OrderSource getOrderSource() {\n   122→        return orderSource;\n   123→    }\n   124→\n   125→    public Location getLocation() {\n   126→        return location;\n   127→    }\n   128→\n   129→    public Instant getTimestamp() {\n   130→        return timestamp;\n   131→    }\n   132→}\n   133→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fccccfb6-6c3c-4161-b41c-50ffcb4f1374","uuid":"6b2d1b08-521f-40df-8beb-385981f5ce27"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01S9i7QqA9AcX2KRnzSwgu2k","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.valueobjects;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonCreator;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonProperty;\n     5→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.Item;\n     6→\n     7→import java.time.Instant;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * A value object encapsulating the information sent to Barista and Kitchen\n    11→ */\n    12→public class OrderIn {\n    13→\n    14→    public final String orderId;\n    15→\n    16→    public final String itemId;\n    17→\n    18→    public final Item item;\n    19→\n    20→    public final String name;\n    21→\n    22→    public final Instant timeIn;\n    23→\n    24→    @JsonCreator(mode = JsonCreator.Mode.PROPERTIES)\n    25→    public OrderIn(\n    26→            @JsonProperty(\"orderId\") String orderId,\n    27→            @JsonProperty(\"lineItemId\") String itemId,\n    28→            @JsonProperty(\"item\") Item item,\n    29→            @JsonProperty(\"name\") String name) {\n    30→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    31→        this.itemId = itemId;\n    32→        this.item = item;\n    33→        this.name = name;\n    34→        this.timeIn = Instant.now();\n    35→    }\n    36→\n    37→    @Override\n    38→    public String toString() {\n    39→        return \"OrderTicket{\" +\n    40→                \"orderId='\" + orderId + '\\'' +\n    41→                \", lineItemId='\" + itemId + '\\'' +\n    42→                \", item=\" + item +\n    43→                \", name='\" + name + '\\'' +\n    44→                \", timestamp=\" + timeIn +\n    45→                '}';\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    @Override\n    49→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    50→        if (this == o) return true;\n    51→        if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;\n    52→\n    53→        OrderIn that = (OrderIn) o;\n    54→\n    55→        if (orderId != null ? !orderId.equals(that.orderId) : that.orderId != null) return false;\n    56→        if (itemId != null ? !itemId.equals(that.itemId) : that.itemId != null) return false;\n    57→        if (item != that.item) return false;\n    58→        if (name != null ? !name.equals(that.name) : that.name != null) return false;\n    59→        return timeIn != null ? timeIn.equals(that.timeIn) : that.timeIn == null;\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    @Override\n    63→    public int hashCode() {\n    64→        int result = orderId != null ? orderId.hashCode() : 0;\n    65→        result = 31 * result + (itemId != null ? itemId.hashCode() : 0);\n    66→        result = 31 * result + (item != null ? item.hashCode() : 0);\n    67→        result = 31 * result + (name != null ? name.hashCode() : 0);\n    68→        result = 31 * result + (timeIn != null ? timeIn.hashCode() : 0);\n    69→        return result;\n    70→    }\n    71→}\n    72→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fccccfb6-6c3c-4161-b41c-50ffcb4f1374","uuid":"7672ba2e-146d-4a10-85f9-2b90a4591ffb"}
