{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HxpKxVSt3isRPgbs6bbzVc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.6-eclipse-temurin-17 AS builder\n     2→\n     3→WORKDIR /app\n     4→COPY pom.xml .\n     5→COPY src ./src\n     6→\n     7→# Build the WAR\n     8→RUN mvn clean package -DskipTests\n     9→\n    10→# Runtime stage - Open Liberty\n    11→FROM icr.io/appcafe/open-liberty:kernel-slim-java17-openj9-ubi\n    12→\n    13→# Add features\n    14→COPY --chown=1001:0 src/main/liberty/config/server.xml /config/server.xml\n    15→\n    16→# Install features based on server.xml\n    17→RUN features.sh\n    18→\n    19→# Copy H2 driver jar for runtime\n    20→ADD --chown=1001:0 https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/h2database/h2/2.2.224/h2-2.2.224.jar /config/lib/h2-2.2.224.jar\n    21→\n    22→# Copy the WAR\n    23→COPY --from=builder --chown=1001:0 /app/target/coffeeshop.war /config/apps/coffeeshop.war\n    24→\n    25→# Copy static resources to the apps directory\n    26→RUN configure.sh\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fccccfb6-6c3c-4161-b41c-50ffcb4f1374","uuid":"34600733-9113-46dd-bc8b-49a281378061"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01C1Rqx8AnM7VaZBkdTjQ4DS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<server description=\"Coffee Shop Jakarta EE Server\">\n     3→\n     4→    <featureManager>\n     5→        <feature>jakartaee-10.0</feature>\n     6→        <feature>microProfile-6.1</feature>\n     7→    </featureManager>\n     8→\n     9→    <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\"\n    10→                  httpPort=\"9080\"\n    11→                  httpsPort=\"9443\"\n    12→                  host=\"*\" />\n    13→\n    14→    <!-- Default datasource using H2 in-memory -->\n    15→    <library id=\"h2Lib\">\n    16→        <fileset dir=\"${server.config.dir}/lib\" includes=\"h2*.jar\"/>\n    17→    </library>\n    18→\n    19→    <dataSource id=\"DefaultDataSource\" jndiName=\"jdbc/coffeeshop\">\n    20→        <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n    21→        <properties.h2.embedded databaseName=\"mem:coffeeshop\" createDatabase=\"true\"/>\n    22→    </dataSource>\n    23→\n    24→    <dataSource id=\"BaristaDataSource\" jndiName=\"jdbc/barista\">\n    25→        <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n    26→        <properties.h2.embedded databaseName=\"mem:barista\" createDatabase=\"true\"/>\n    27→    </dataSource>\n    28→\n    29→    <dataSource id=\"KitchenDataSource\" jndiName=\"jdbc/kitchen\">\n    30→        <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n    31→        <properties.h2.embedded databaseName=\"mem:kitchen\" createDatabase=\"true\"/>\n    32→    </dataSource>\n    33→\n    34→    <webApplication location=\"coffeeshop.war\" contextRoot=\"/\">\n    35→        <classloader commonLibraryRef=\"h2Lib\"/>\n    36→    </webApplication>\n    37→\n    38→    <logging consoleLogLevel=\"INFO\" />\n    39→</server>\n    40→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fccccfb6-6c3c-4161-b41c-50ffcb4f1374","uuid":"314ddf4f-aea4-4c27-9f14-b5f2577e016a"}
